tafsir[7]{c,v,t}:
  74,1,"And from his narration on the authority of Ibn 'Abbas that he said regarding the interpretation of Allah's saying (O thou enveloped in your cloak): '(O thou enveloped in your cloak) addressing the Prophet (pbuh) who had enveloped himself in his cloak to sleep"
  74,2,"(Arise and warn!) warn people and call them to profess Allah's divine Oneness."
  74,5,"(Pollution shun!) shun all sins and do not go near them."
  74,13,"(And sons abiding in his presence) never out of his sight. He had ten sons."
  74,14,"(And made (life) smooth for him) he had his wealth piled up just as one piles up couches on top of each other."
  74,15,"(Yet he) i.e. al-Walid (desireth that I should give more) wealth while disobeying and disbelieving in Me."
  74,16,"(Nay!) I will not give him more. And since then his wealth kept decreasing. (For lo! He) i.e. al-Walid Ibn al-Mughirah (hath been stubborn to Our revelations) to Our Scripture and Messenger; he turned away from them in disbelief."